Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim woody
bottom ends from @Asparagus{8%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{5%teaspoon},
half the @Autumn Spice Blend{1/2%tablespoon} (use all the spice for 4 servings),
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss asparagus on a second baking sheet with a large drizzle
of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast potatoes on top rack and asparagus on middle rack
until tender and crisped, ~{10-12%minutes} for asparagus and ~{30%minutes} for
potatoes.

Meanwhile, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat;
transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While pork cooks, halve, core, and dice @Apple{1} into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and
dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{} and melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for pork
over medium heat. Add onion and cook until lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add apple
and @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce}. Cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in
@Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @Cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}.
Cook, stirring, until apple is tender but not mushy, about ~{4%minutes}.
> Add a splash of water if mixture is dry. Stir in any resting juices from pork.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide potatoes, asparagus, and pork between plates. Top pork with pan sauce, making
sure to include apple and cranberries. Garnish with parsley and serve.